cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about a new architecture for natural language processing tasks, specifically for the Transformer model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the reduction of model complexity, which suggests that it could be relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper includes experiments on image captioning, which could also make it relevant to computer vision (cs.CV).
